  "text": "To gain more insight into molecular bases of DNA rearrangement pathways of mouse-growing oocytes and early embryos, we studied in detail the DNA 5Ј 3 3Ј exonuclease and NHEJ activities of these cells. 5Ј 3 3Ј Exonuclease is a key activity for SSA in Xenopus oocytes [CITATION_1] . To overcome the limited availability of mammalian oocytes and preimplantation embryos, we devised a novel asymmetric PCR assay that allowed us to simultaneously detect both DNA 5Ј 3 3Ј exonuclease and NHEJ activities on small numbers of living oocytes and embryos. To this end, growing oocytes and late one-cell embryos received an intranuclear injection of 10,000 copies/GV or pronucleus of a blunt-ended, 895-bp DNA",
